<p><b>Recent Literature</b></p>
<p><a href="../abstracts/lit1/819.shtm"><img src="../abstracts/lit1/819a.gif"></a><br>
<i>para</i>-Formylation of nitroarenes via vicarious nucleophilic substitution of 
hydrogen with tris(benzotriazol-1-yl)methane<br>
A. R. Katritzky, L. Xie, <i>Tetrahedron Lett.</i>, <b>1996</b>,
<i>37</i>, 347-350.</p>
<p><a href="../abstracts/lit1/817.shtm"><img src="../abstracts/lit1/817a.gif"></a><br>
1,1,1-Trimethylhydrazinium Iodide: A Novel, Highly Reactive Reagent for 
Aromatic Amination via Vicarious Nucleophilic Substitution of Hydrogen<br>
P. F. Pagoria, A. R. Mitchell, R. D. Schmidt, <i>J. Org. Chem.</i>, <b>1996</b>,
<i>61</i>, 2934-2935.</p>
<p><a href="../abstracts/lit1/815.shtm"><img src="../abstracts/lit1/815a.gif"></a><br>
Hydroxylation of Nitroarenes with Alkyl Hydroperoxide Anions via Vicarious 
Nucleophilic Substitution of Hydrogen<br>
M. Makosza, K. Sienkiewicz, <i>J. Org. Chem.</i>, <b>1998</b>,
<i>63</i>, 4199-4208.</p>
